      - status: stable
        content:
          name: CorrelationReturnTerms
          namespace:
            type:
              blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
            value: cdm/product/asset
          annualizationFactor:
            description: |
              This specifies the numerator of an annualization factor. Frequently this number is equal to the number of observations of prices in a year e.g. 252.
            type:
              blueId: 5WNMiV9Knz63B4dVY5JtMyh3FB4FSGqv7ceScvuapdE1
          boundedCorrelation:
            description: Describes correlation bounds, which form a cap and a floor on the realized correlation.
            type:
              blueId: 7eQNHwy255BHnoBffoqVyHQuu4yDiZuRdQqRFnz6B2nc
          correlationStrikePrice:
            description: Correlation Strike Price in accordance with the ISDA 2011 Equity Derivatives Definitions.
            type:
              blueId: 34JSSaiNLZkZGJCPhZGY4wsFrAd7HeP7M2MEwHXHZp2u
            schema:
              required:
                type:
                  blueId: 4EzhSubEimSQD3zrYHRtobfPPWntUuhEz8YcdxHsi12u
                value: true
          dividendApplicability:
            description: The parameters which define whether dividends are applicable
            type:
              blueId: 7YPXekUAnhSyp9AcFCEqPbCAU21zbcDE5gTMTqxEu6f4
          equityUnderlierProvisions:
            description: Contains Equity Underlyer provisions regarding jurisdiction and fallbacks.
            type:
              blueId: 68bTDtRvgynPZurH7nT19Jy72N8v8n4ZcDksksPDZ3pd
          expectedN:
            description: Expected number of trading days.
            type:
              blueId: 5WNMiV9Knz63B4dVY5JtMyh3FB4FSGqv7ceScvuapdE1
          initialLevel:
            description: |
              Contract will strike off this initial level. Providing just the initialLevel without initialLevelSource, infers that this is AgreedInitialPrice - a specified Initial Index Level.
            type:
              blueId: 7pwXmXYCJtWnd348c2JQGBkm9C4renmZRwxbfaypsx5y
          initialLevelSource:
            description: In this context, this is AgreedInitialPrice - a specified Initial Index Level.
            type:
              blueId: A4xQ1M4K4Bxgfj42oJzfRc6Jc8n5qjBuZW3DA5zJEgMy
          meanAdjustment:
            description: |
              Specifies whether Mean Adjustment is applicable or not in the calculation of the Realized Volatility, Variance or Correlation
            type:
              blueId: 4EzhSubEimSQD3zrYHRtobfPPWntUuhEz8YcdxHsi12u
          numberOfDataSeries:
            description: |
              Number of data series, normal market practice is that correlation data sets are drawn from geographic market areas, such as America, Europe and Asia Pacific, each of these geographic areas will have its own data series to avoid contagion.
            type:
              blueId: 5WNMiV9Knz63B4dVY5JtMyh3FB4FSGqv7ceScvuapdE1
          performance:
            description: |
              Performance calculation, in accordance with Part 1 Section 12 of the 2018 ISDA CDM Equity Confirmation for Security Equity Swap, Para 75. 'Equity Performance'. Cumulative performance is used as a notional multiplier factor on both legs of an Equity Swap.
            type:
              blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
          sharePriceDividendAdjustment:
            description: Indicates whether the price of shares is adjusted for dividends or not.
            type:
              blueId: 4EzhSubEimSQD3zrYHRtobfPPWntUuhEz8YcdxHsi12u
          valuationTerms:
            description: Contains all non-date valuation information.
            type:
              blueId: HBPyekApP6oSxJLXSqMqQEf4uuZaocEC84epkGmriddV
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 3
            typeBlueId: CyS1jyBo91Y2jhQEtVGjRBBUKjzwGpH9gBYgtTuatqBk
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: Counterparty
          description: |
            Defines a counterparty enumerated value, e.g. Party1 or Party2, with an associated party reference. The product is agnostic to the actual parties to the transaction, with the party references abstracted away from the product definition and replaced by the CounterpartyEnum (e.g. values Party1 or Party2). The CounterpartyEnum can then be positioned in the product (e.g. to specify which counterparty is the payer, receiver etc) and this Counterparty type, which is positioned outside of the product definition, allows the CounterpartyEnum to be associated with an actual party reference.
          namespace:
            type:
              blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
            value: cdm/base/staticdata/party
          partyReference:
            description: Specifies the party that is associated to the counterparty.
            type:
              blueId: DVG4WkiKTRaHwt4MUfbHBGMX2YwcBypUv2HBVkEJGyse
            schema:
              required:
                type:
                  blueId: 4EzhSubEimSQD3zrYHRtobfPPWntUuhEz8YcdxHsi12u
                value: true
          role:
            description: Specifies the CounterpartyEnum, e.g. either Party1 or Party2, that is associated to the partyReference.
            type:
              blueId: 7LtrDiGHU2GXVifkZ35wubNV3qNSidQE4TxhiNyudXj
            schema:
              required:
                type:
                  blueId: 4EzhSubEimSQD3zrYHRtobfPPWntUuhEz8YcdxHsi12u
                value: true
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 3
            typeBlueId: gfoywborZ3FfKnSaoNBtFq5TPCXFpfJKuQ2AD1nAs47
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: CounterpartyOwnIssuePermitted
          namespace:
            type:
              blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
            value: cdm/product/collateral
          counterpartyOwnIssuePermitted:
            description: |
              Represents a filter based on whether it is permitted for the underlying asset to be issued by the posting entity or part of their corporate family.
