      - status: stable
        content:
          name: MasterAgreementClauseVariant
          description: Sets the details for a specific variant associated to a clause in a Master Agreement
          namespace:
            type:
              blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
            value: cdm/legaldocumentation/master
          counterparty:
            description: |
              Optional counterparty role. This can be used where a clause needs to assign a different variant to the different parties on the agreement based upon their role i.e. Party A or Party B.
            type:
              blueId: 6aehfNAxHLC1PHHoDr3tYtFH3RWNbiWdFancJ1bypXEY
            itemType:
              blueId: 7LtrDiGHU2GXVifkZ35wubNV3qNSidQE4TxhiNyudXj
            schema:
              minItems:
                type:
                  blueId: 5WNMiV9Knz63B4dVY5JtMyh3FB4FSGqv7ceScvuapdE1
                value: 0
              maxItems:
                type:
                  blueId: 5WNMiV9Knz63B4dVY5JtMyh3FB4FSGqv7ceScvuapdE1
                value: 2
          identifier:
            description: Unique identifier for this variant
            type:
              blueId: 41Su5SkQUFTSWLFcACHf8vaUTy7SEuvynt982wsfAC62
            schema:
              required:
                type:
                  blueId: 4EzhSubEimSQD3zrYHRtobfPPWntUuhEz8YcdxHsi12u
                value: true
          otherParty:
            description: |
              Optional party. This can be used where a clause needs to assign different variants to different parties who may or may not be on the agreement.
            type:
              blueId: 6aehfNAxHLC1PHHoDr3tYtFH3RWNbiWdFancJ1bypXEY
            itemType:
              blueId: G5qdV1cr23CKFp5rHm6dGo9ucFp3Lae5UrRwWRTkC7gh
            schema:
              minItems:
                type:
                  blueId: 5WNMiV9Knz63B4dVY5JtMyh3FB4FSGqv7ceScvuapdE1
                value: 0
          variableSet:
            description: |
              For some variants of some clauses additional details are required to work out what has been elected. This array can be used to define the name and value of these variables. Please refer to the agreement documentation for more details of the variables that are available for any clause.
            type:
              blueId: 6aehfNAxHLC1PHHoDr3tYtFH3RWNbiWdFancJ1bypXEY
            itemType:
              blueId: 7Sjs1Em9GMV1CPrHj4cGL7ZgqmaTj2qyqfA2hUkTD21u#0
            schema:
              minItems:
                type:
                  blueId: 5WNMiV9Knz63B4dVY5JtMyh3FB4FSGqv7ceScvuapdE1
                value: 0
